<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I"><UNDER>AFFIDAVIT</UNDER></TI>
<P>I, Robert Jewett of the City of Mississauga and Province of Ontario, <BOLD>SWEAR THAT</BOLD>:
<P1>1. I am the Applicant in this matter. As such, I have personal knowledge of the matters herein deposed to, save and except where stated to be on information from others, and where so stated, I believe that information to be true.</P1></P></BLOCK1>
<BLOCK1><TI>First Notice of Objection</TI>
<P>2. On February 01, 2008, I was assessed by the Minister of National Revenue (the &ldquo;<BOLD>Minister</BOLD>&rdquo;) under s. 152(7) of the <EM>Income Tax Act</EM> (R.S.C., 1985 c. 1 (5<SUP>th</SUP> Supp.), the &ldquo;<BOLD>ITA</BOLD>&rdquo;) for the 2002 and 2003 tax years (attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P>
<P>3. On May 02, 2008, my then lawyer&mdash;Mr. John David Boute&mdash;filed an Application for an Extension of Time to file a Notice of Objection for the 2002 and 2003 tax years (the &ldquo;<BOLD>First Objection</BOLD>&rdquo;, attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P>
<P>4. At the time of filing the First Objection, Mr. Boute requested that this matter be held in abeyance pending the resolution of my appeal in the Tax Court of Canada for the 1999 to 2001 tax years on the grounds that there were common issues in all of the years (the &ldquo;<BOLD>TCC Appeal</BOLD>&rdquo;, see Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo;).</P>
<P>5. On February 18, 2009, the appeals officer assigned to my file, Ms. Alice Tao (&ldquo;<BOLD>Appeals Officer Tao</BOLD>&rdquo;), requested that I prepare and submit T1 income tax returns for the 2002 tax year for her review (attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P>
<P>6. On June 25, 2009, the Minister issued Notice of Confirmation for my 2002 tax year (the &ldquo;<BOLD>Confirmation</BOLD>&rdquo;, attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;D&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P></BLOCK1>
<BLOCK1><TI>Tax Court of Canada Decision for 1999 to 2001</TI>
<P>7. On November 20, 2009, the Tax Court of Canada rendered its decision with respect to the TCC Appeal (attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;E&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P></BLOCK1>
<BLOCK1><TI>Second Notice of Objection</TI>
<P>8. On April 08, 2010, a consequential reassessment for the 2002 tax year was issued as a result of the decision in the TCC Appeal (attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;F&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P>
<P>9. On June 24, 2011, my new lawyer&mdash;Mr. Nick Ranieri&mdash;filed an Application for an Extension of Time to file a Notice of Objection for the 1999 to 2003 and 2009 tax years (the &ldquo;<BOLD>Second Objection</BOLD>&rdquo;, attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;G&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>ITA s. 165(1.2) Applied to 2002 Tax Year</EM></TI>
<P><P1>10. On January 04, 2012, the Canada Revenue Agency (the &ldquo;<BOLD>CRA</BOLD>&rdquo;) acknowledged receipt of the Second Objection and refused to accept the objection for the 2002 tax year citing the application of ITA s. 165(1.2) (attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit</BOLD> &ldquo;H&rdquo;).</P1>
<P1>11. On August 10, 2012, an appeals officer&mdash;Ms. Maryam Aman (&ldquo;<BOLD>Appeals Officer Aman</BOLD>&rdquo;)&mdash;requested particulars in respect of my objection for the 2009 tax year only (attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;I&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P1>
<P1>12. On December 19, 2012, a new appeals officer&mdash;Ms. Hanaa Farag (&ldquo;<BOLD>Appeals Officer Farag</BOLD>&rdquo;)&mdash;was assigned to the Second Objection (attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;J&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P1>
<P1>13. On January 14, 2013, Mr. Ranieri wrote to Appeals Officer Farag stating that ITA s. 165(1.2) was inapplicable to my 2002 tax year (attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;K&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P1>
<P1>14. On January 15, 2013, Appeals Officer Farag wrote to Mr. Ranieri to request further information and explanations (attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;L&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P1>
<P1>15. On February 01, 2013, Mr. Ranieri in response to Appeals Officer Farag's January 15, 2013 letter, again repeated his submission that ITA s. 165(1.2) was not applicable to my 2002 tax year (attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;M&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P1></P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>ITA s. 165(1.2) Inapplicable to 2002 Tax Year</EM></TI>
<P><P1>16. On March 5, 2013, Appeals Officer Farag informed me that the CRA was now in agreement with me. They agreed that the objection for the 2002 tax year was valid as a result of a consequential reassessment stemming from the TCC Appeal (attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;N&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P1>
<P1>17. On April 10, 2013, Mr. Ranieri submitted my T1 income tax returns for the 2002 tax year to Appeals Officer Farag by fax (attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;O&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P1>
<P1>18. I acknowledge Exhibit &ldquo;O&rdquo; appears incomplete as it only has page 1 of my 2003 T1 income tax return. However, it is my understanding that the CRA was already in possession of my 2003 T1 returns at the time of Mr. Ranieri's letter dated April 10, 2013 as a copy of said return dated March 20, 2012 was found in an <EM>Access to Information Act</EM> disclosure from the CRA made to me on June 14, 2016 (attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;P&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P1>
<P1>19. On April 12, 2013, Appeals Officer Farag provided Mr. Ranieri with a final summary of the Notices of Objection for the 1999 through 2002 tax years (attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;Q&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P1>
<P1>20. On February 03, 2014, Mr. Ranieri filed a request for a reassessment pursuant to ITA s. 152(4.2) for my 2002 tax year (attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit</BOLD> &ldquo;R&rdquo;).</P1>
<P1>21. On May 05, 2014, Appeals Officer Aman requested that I provide supporting documentation with respect to the 2002 tax year (attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;S&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P1>
<P1>22. On June 04, 2014, Mr. Ranieri provided Appeals Officer Aman with financial statements indicating my pay in the 2002 tax year (attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;T&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P1>
<P1>23. On the same day, Mr. Ranieri wrote to Appeals Officer Aman to provide written confirmation of my position with respect to the 2002 tax year (attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;U&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P1></P></BLOCK2></BLOCK1>
<BLOCK1><TI>First Taxpayer Relief Request Filed</TI>
<P>24. On July 03, 2014, I filed a Request for Taxpayer Relief for the 2002 tax year on the basis that the CRA had made a delay in processing my objection and that my then lawyer, Mr. Boute, had misinformed me about filing an appeal for the 2003 tax year (the &ldquo;<BOLD>First Relief Request</BOLD>&rdquo;, attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;V&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P></BLOCK1>
<BLOCK1><TI>Second Notice of Objection Allowed in Part</TI>
<P>25. On July 24, 2014, the CRA allowed my 2002 tax year objection in part (attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;W&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P></BLOCK1>
<BLOCK1><TI>CRA Response to the First Taxpayer Relief Request</TI>
<P>26. On May 07, 2015, the CRA rejected the First Relief Request for the following reasons:
<P1>a. a history of non-compliance with my tax obligations;</P1>
<P1>b. a balance had knowingly been allowed to exist on which arrears interest had accrued;</P1>
<P1>c. a reasonable amount of care had not been exercised; and</P1>
<P1>d. actions were not taken to quickly remedy any delay or omission.
<P2>(May 07, 2015 CRA letter attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;X&rdquo;</BOLD>)</P2></P1></P></BLOCK1>
<BLOCK1><TI>Second Taxpayer Relief Request Filed</TI>
<P>27. On May 25, 2016, TaxChambers LLP filed, on behalf of myself, another Taxpayer Relief Request (the &ldquo;<BOLD>Second Relief Request</BOLD>&rdquo;, attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;Y&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P>
<P>28. The Second Relief Request asked for two types of relief:
<P1>a. the cancellation of interest that accrued from May 25, 2006 to May 25, 2016 on any balance in respect of the 2002 and 2003 tax years; and</P1>
<P1>b. the waiver of all future interest on any balance in respect of the 2002 and 2003 tax years.</P1></P>
<P>29. On December 05, 2016, the CRA responded to the Second Relief Request as follows:
<P1>a. Arrears interest for the 2002 tax year was cancelled for the period between June 24, 2011 and March 06, 2013 due to possible CRA delay (&ldquo;<BOLD>Second Request Decision</BOLD>&rdquo;).</P1>
<P1>b. All other requested relief was denied. In particular:
<P2>i. no relief was granted for the 2002 tax year from January 01, 2006 to June 24, 2011;</P2>
<P2>ii. no relief was granted for the 2002 tax year from March 5, 2013 to October 5, 2016;</P2>
<P2>iii. no relief was granted for the 2003 tax year from January 01, 2006 to the present; and</P2>
<P2>iv. no agreement to waive any interest that would otherwise accrue on the 2002 and 2003 tax years starting on May 25, 2016.</P2></P1>
<P1>(December 05, 2016 CRA letter attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;Z&rdquo;</BOLD>)</P1></P></BLOCK1>
<BLOCK1><TI>Second Level Review of Second Relief Request</TI>
<P>30. On May 04, 2017, TaxChambers LLP filed, on behalf of myself, a second level review of the Second Request Decision (the &ldquo;<BOLD>Second Level Review Request</BOLD>&rdquo; attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;AA&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P>
<P>31. The Second Level Review Request asked for two types of relief:
<P1>a. the cancellation of interest that accrued in respect of the 2002 and 2003 tax years for the following periods:
<P2>i. from May 25, 2006 to June 24, 2011; and</P2>
<P2>ii. from March 6, 2013 to the present date.</P2></P1>
<P1>b. the waiver of all future interest on any balance in respect of the 2002 and 2003 tax years.
<P2>(See Exhibit &ldquo;AA&rdquo;)</P2></P1></P>
<P>32. On July 19, 2017, the CRA responded to the Second Level Review request as follows:
<P1>a. Arrears interest for the 2002 and 2003 taxation years were cancelled for the period between May 2, 2008 and June 24, 2011 due to the actions of the CRA (the &ldquo;<BOLD>Second Level Review Response</BOLD>&rdquo;).</P1>
<P1>b. All other requested relief was denied. In particular:
<P2>i. no relief was granted for the 2002 tax year from January 01, 2006 to May 1, 2008;</P2>
<P2>ii. no relief was granted for the 2002 tax year from March 5, 2013 to October 5, 2016;</P2>
<P2>iii. no relief was granted for the 2003 tax year from January 01, 2006 to May 1, 2008;</P2>
<P2>iv. no relief was granted for the 2003 tax year from June 25, 2011 to October 5, 2016;and</P2>
<P2>v. no agreement to waive any interest that would otherwise accrue on the 2002 and 2003 tax years starting on May 25, 2016.</P2></P1>
<P1>(July 19, 2017 CRA letter attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;BB&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P1></P></BLOCK1>
