<BLOCK1><TI>AFFIDAVIT</TI>
<P>I, Tracey MacGregor, of the City of Summerside, in the Province of Prince Edward Island, MAKE OATH AND SAY:</P>
<P>1. I am a Taxpayer Relief Officer, Appeals Branch, at the Prince Edward Island Tax Centre of the Canada Revenue Agency (CRA) and as such have personal knowledge of the matters hereinafter deposed to, save and except what is stated to be on information and belief, and where so stated, I verily believe them to be true. Where I refer to information herein without expressly disclosing the source, the information was derived from my review of the CRA records for the applicant, Robert Jewett.</P>
<BLOCK2><TI>Taxpayer Relief Provisions</TI>
<P>2. Pursuant to subsection 220(3.1) of the <EM>Income Tax Act</EM>, R.S.C. 1985, c. 1 (5th Supp.), as amended (the &ldquo;<EM>Act</EM>&rdquo;), the Minister of National Revenue (the &ldquo;Minister&rdquo;) has discretion to waive interest or penalties (&ldquo;Taxpayer Relief&rdquo;). The Minister's discretion in respect of Taxpayer Relief is exercised by officials at the CRA with the requisite delegated authority.</P>
<P>3. Ms. Lori Beck, Team Leader, Taxpayer Relief Centre of Expertise, Appeals Branch, at the Prince Edward Island Tax Centre, is one of the CRA officials with the requisite delegated authority to exercise the Minister's discretion in respect of Taxpayer Relief. I am an officer in Ms. Beck's team.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI>First Request for Relief and Decision</TI>
<P>4. In May 2016, the applicant made a request to the Minister for Taxpayer Relief for waiver of interest and penalties in respect of his 2002 and 2003 taxation years. The request was received by the Minister on May 30, 2016.</P>
<P>5. Upon receiving the applicant's request, John Asche, an officer of the Taxpayer Relief Centre of Expertise, Appeals Branch at the Vancouver Tax Services Office (TSO) was designated to conduct a review of the request and to prepare a report for review by the ultimate decision maker. Mr. Asche prepared a report wherein he set out his review of the facts and his recommendations with respect to the applicant's request. Attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of Mr. Asche's report.</P>
<P>6. Shelley O'Connor, a team leader of the Taxpayer Relief Centre of Expertise, Appeals Branch at the Vancouver TSO, was a CRA officer with requisite delegated authority to exercise the Minister's discretion in respect of Taxpayer Relief, and the ultimate decision maker in respect of the applicant's request. She agreed with Mr. Asche's recommendations and made the decision to partially approve the applicant's request for Taxpayer Relief. Attached as hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of the letter from Ms. O'Connor to Robert Jewett, dated December 5, 2016, advising him that his request for Taxpayer Relief has been partially approved.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI>Second Request for Relief, Review of Request and Decision</TI>
<P>7. In May 2017, the applicant made a request for the Minister to reconsider Ms. O'Connor's decision with respect to his request for Taxpayer Relief for his 2002 and 2003 taxation years. The request was received by the Minister on May 4, 2017 (the &ldquo;Second Review Request&rdquo;).</P>
<P>8. I was the officer designated to review the Second Review Request and to prepare a report with my recommendations for review by the ultimate decision maker. Attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of my report.</P>
<P>9. In making my recommendations with respect to the Second Review Request, I carefully reviewed the following documents and information:
<P1>a. the CRA records for the applicant referenced or relied upon in my report;</P1>
<P1>b. the correspondence related to the applicant; and</P1>
<P1>c. the applicant's materials and submissions in the request dated May 4, 2017;</P1>
attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;D&rdquo;</BOLD> are copies of the CRA OP N.4 printouts (CRA electronic records for taxpayer's history of filings, reassessments and payments) in respect of Robert Jewett's 2002 taxation year. Attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;E&rdquo;</BOLD> are copies of the CRA OP N.4 printouts (CRA electronic records for taxpayer's history of filings, reassessments and payments) in respect of Robert Jewett's 2003 taxation year. Attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;F&rdquo;</BOLD> are copies CRA Enforcement Action History printouts (&ldquo;SUDS&rdquo;) in respect of Robert Jewett's 2002 and 2003 taxation years. Attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;G&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of CRA list of correspondence issued to Robert Jewett from Revenue Collections printout (&ldquo;REMITS&rdquo;). Attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;H&rdquo;</BOLD> are copies of CRA collections diary printouts (&ldquo;ACSES&rdquo;) in respect of Robert Jewett ranging from the beginning of January 2003 to the end of December 2016. Attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;I&rdquo;</BOLD> are reproductions of correspondence from CRA electronic records (&ldquo;ELCS&rdquo;) in respect of Robert Jewett.</P>
<P>10. After my review of the documents and information, I recommended granting relief of the arrears interest assessed on the applicant's 2002 and 2003 taxation years from May 2, 2008 up to June 24, 2011, due to CRA delay.</P>
<P>11. In coming to my recommendation for granting the applicant partial interest relief, I considered carefully the circumstances of the applicant, and concluded that the applicant was prevented from meeting his payment obligations due to some CRA delay, and in particular:
<ITEM><P>on May 2, 2008, the applicant served his request for an extension of time to file objections to the Minister's reassessments for his 2002 and 2003 taxation years;</P></ITEM>
<ITEM><P>on August 20, 2008, the applicant served his objections to the Minister's reassessments for his 2002 and 2003 taxation years;</P></ITEM>
<ITEM><P>on February 18, 2009, CRA acknowledge receipt of the applicant's objections for his 2002 and 2003 taxation years;</P></ITEM>
<ITEM><P>on or about October 26, 2009, CRA closed the file for the applicant's objections for his 2002 and 2003 taxation years;</P></ITEM>
<ITEM><P>in May/June 2010, CRA officers incorrectly advised the applicant, in writing and verbally in a telephone call, that the applicant's objections for the 2002 and 2003 taxation years remained active and under review; and</P></ITEM>
<ITEM><P>on June 24, 2011, the applicant served second objections for his 2002 and 2003 taxation years.</P></ITEM></P>
<P>12. In coming to my recommendation for granting the applicant partial interest relief, I also confirmed and considered the fact that the applicant has been granted relief of the arrears interest assessed on his 2002 and 2003 taxation years from June 24, 2011, to March 5, 2013, due to CRA delay pursuant to his first request for Taxpayer Relief.</P>
<P>13. My recommendations with respect to the Second Review Request was submitted for review by Mr. Dean Rush and Ms. Beck. Mr. Rush and Ms. Beck agreed with my recommendation to grant partial interest relief. The decision and reasons were communicated to the applicant by letter. Attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;J&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of the letter from Lori Beck to Robert Jewett dated July 19, 2017.</P>
